    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nNo\n\n### Feature description\n\nAwesome work guys :sunglasses: \r\n\r\nIt would be nice to have highlighting on delete, move (cut) or change similarily to highlighting on yank, e.g. using `d3w` would show a brief highlight and then delete. This would be useful as a confirmation that the right range of text was deleted/moved/changed.\r\n\r\nBy move I mean the following remap:\r\n```vim\r\nPlug 'svermeulen/vim-cutlass'  \" delete without affecting yank\r\nnnoremap m d\r\nxnoremap m d\r\nnnoremap mm dd\r\nnnoremap M D\r\n```\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2022-04-26T16:22:31Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "What would be the use case? Yank operations would be invisible otherwise, but you can clearly see what is being deleted without the highlight. (Yank is also special since there's already a `TextYankPost` event that exposes all the necessary info; this is not necessarily the case for other operations.)",
